        <p><span>Sustainable ways of life are the need of the hour world over. Various changes at the individual, as well as communal level, come across every day. Various debates and discussions by revolutionaries like Greta Thunberg have brought about revolutions like banning plastic cutlery. Plastic straws and cups have now been replaced with paper cups, spoons and forks with wooden substitutes. However, with the one-time kind of usage that they have, most of them end up in garbage dumps and landfills. </span></p>
        <p><span>Can you imagine a solution to exist that is bio-degradable and hence, environment friendly, adds to the nutritional value of food and despite all these miraculous benefits is economical still? The answer to all our doubts is finally here: The edible cutlery. You can now fill up on additional contents, flavours and nutrients with every meal when having anything using edible cutlery!&nbsp; Edible cutlery is literally made up of ingredients with the natural goodness of healthy food options of multi-grains like oats, ragi, millets and chickpea. It is absolutely perfect to throw in for a complete meal, deserts and ice creams or for simply pairing up with evening snacking options warm soups or broth. Edible cutlery is a promise for your health as it is made up of 100% natural ingredients with no added sugar and preservatives, and has a shelf life of up to 12 months</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>
        <p class="points-heading"><strong>Why choose edible cutlery for eating?</strong></p>
        <p><span>We&rsquo;re now well acquainted with how wonderful the edible cutlery is for the environment given their biodegradable property and how they can propel a greener, cleaner and more sustainable future. Let&rsquo;s dive a little deeper into the question of why should you switch to edible cutlery over plastic disposables almost immediately:</span></p>
        <ul class="ul-style-type">
            <li>Made from 100% pure and natural ingredients, edible cutlery items are absolutely natural without any chemicals in form of preservatives.</li>
            <li>Even though there&rsquo;s a notion of how can edible items last as long as plastic or conventional metal cutlery on the shelf, the edible cutlery is made with the least quantity of water possible and hence, has almost no moisture, or fat content. All these make for it to have a long shelf life without any additional preservatives.</li>
            <li>Since these tastes well and have no preservatives, edible cutlery items are children and toddler-proof.</li>
            <li>An easy and economical replacement for the current disposable utensils on the market.</li>
            <li>Edible cutlery is multi-purpose in nature and can be used to eat a vast variety of cuisines and everything from snacks to square meals and deserts</li>
            <li>In case the edible cutlery is not consumed for a long time and pass their expiration (a year), it is able to degrade on its own, you can simply soak it into the water until it dissolves or can be used it in manure for plants.</li>
            <li>Edible utensils come in various shapes and sizes such as spoons, forks, or even chopsticks.</li>
            <li>Edible utensils help limit the use of plastics, resulting in the reduction of plastic waste.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="points-heading"><strong>Where can edible cutlery be used?</strong></p>
        <p><span>Edible cutlery as we have seen has a very versatile spectrum of usage. Let&rsquo;s take a sneak peek into its various uses:</span></p>
        <ul class="ul-style-type">
            <li><span> </span><span>Edible cutlery can be used by cohorts of all ages and locations. It is so safe that it is children and toddler friendly.</span></li>
            <li><span> </span><span>Edible cutlery can be used in various places, in any type of setting like a takeaway or be carried along with to a camping trip. It makes an excellent alternative and substitutes for plastic and wooden cutlery.</span></li>
            <li><span> </span><span>Lastly, edible cutlery can be used for eating various types of cuisines and meals like snacks, desserts, salad, soups etc.</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="points-heading"><strong>How it can be a better alternative than plastic spoons?</strong></p>
